{
  "page": "Paramour",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Sedone_Thongvilay_Paramour.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/9/9d/Sedone_Thongvilay_Paramour.jpg/350px-Sedone_Thongvilay_Paramour.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"263\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/9/9d/Sedone_Thongvilay_Paramour.jpg/525px-Sedone_Thongvilay_Paramour.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/9/9d/Sedone_Thongvilay_Paramour.jpg/700px-Sedone_Thongvilay_Paramour.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Sedone_Thongvilay_Paramour.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A paramour, by Sedone Thongvilay © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>A <b>paramour</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> or <b>mistress</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos24.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> is the unmarried lover of a <a href=\"/index.php/Nobility\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Nobility\">noble</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Culture</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Known_paramours\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Known paramours</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Culture\">Culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Paramour&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Culture\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Xia_TaptaraJealousParamour.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/42/Xia_TaptaraJealousParamour.jpg/350px-Xia_TaptaraJealousParamour.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"300\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/4/42/Xia_TaptaraJealousParamour.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Xia_TaptaraJealousParamour.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>A jealous paramour, by Xia Taptara © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>In <a href=\"/index.php/Dorne\" title=\"Dorne\">Dorne</a>, it is common for <a href=\"/index.php/Lord\" title=\"Lord\">lords</a> and ladies to have paramours, chosen out of love and lust rather than political alliances. <a href=\"/index.php/Dornishmen\" title=\"Dornishmen\">Dornishmen</a> are not greatly concerned if a <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a> is born to a paramour.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf795_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf795-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Dorne gives a degree of social status to paramours, despite the \"unchaste\" nature of the relationship. Outside of Dorne, a Dornish paramour's status is less certain. They may be afforded the esteem granted in their homeland by the diplomatic-minded, or they may receive treatment ranging from slight social disdain to moral condemnation.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>That same varying treatment also applies to paramours of non-Dornish nobles, even the mistresses of kings.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf411.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf411.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> A paramour can be of the same sex as their lover.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Each partner in a marriage can have their own paramour, though it depends on the rank of the partners.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rssm1285.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rssm1285.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Citadel\" title=\"Citadel\">Citadel</a> does not allow its novices to keep wives or paramours, at least not openly.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Paramour&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>When Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Lyonel_Hightower\" title=\"Lyonel Hightower\">Lyonel Hightower</a> was forbidden by the <a href=\"/index.php/High_Septon\" title=\"High Septon\">High Septon</a> from marrying his widowed step-mother, <a href=\"/index.php/Samantha_Tarly\" title=\"Samantha Tarly\">Samantha Tarly</a>, he kept her as a paramour and fathered six children on her, before the election of a new High Septon allowed their marriage. The relationship was deemed highly scandalous.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>It was a closely held secret that Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Lewyn_Martell\" title=\"Lewyn Martell\">Lewyn Martell</a> kept a paramour despite the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a> oaths of chastity.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Barristan_Selmy\" title=\"Barristan Selmy\">Barristan Selmy</a> and his other sworn brothers were aware of this, but kept his secret.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Selwyn_Tarth\" title=\"Selwyn Tarth\">Selwyn Tarth</a>'s wife died, he kept a new \"lady\" every year.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Paramour&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Paramour&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Drazenka_Kimpel_Ellaria_Sand.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/32/Drazenka_Kimpel_Ellaria_Sand.JPG/350px-Drazenka_Kimpel_Ellaria_Sand.JPG\" width=\"350\" height=\"288\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/3/32/Drazenka_Kimpel_Ellaria_Sand.JPG 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Drazenka_Kimpel_Ellaria_Sand.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">Oberyn Martell</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Ellaria_Sand\" title=\"Ellaria Sand\">Ellaria Sand</a>, by Drazenka Kimpel © Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<p>A degree of social deference is given to <a href=\"/index.php/Ellaria_Sand\" title=\"Ellaria Sand\">Ellaria Sand</a> by virtue of her relationship with Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Oberyn_Martell\" title=\"Oberyn Martell\">Oberyn Martell</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> While esteemed as a high-ranking woman by the <a href=\"/index.php/Dornishmen\" title=\"Dornishmen\">Dornishmen</a>, in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> her presence at the high table at the <a href=\"/index.php/Purple_Wedding\" title=\"Purple Wedding\">royal wedding</a> of King <a href=\"/index.php/Joffrey_Baratheon\" title=\"Joffrey Baratheon\">Joffrey I Baratheon</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Margaery_Tyrell\" title=\"Margaery Tyrell\">Margaery Tyrell</a> would be taken as an insult by the noblewomen seated near her. Ellaria is instead placed at a place of honor near the dais.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos38.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Olenna_Redwyne\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Olenna Redwyne\">Olenna Redwyne</a> refers to her as \"the <a href=\"/index.php/Serpent\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Serpent\">serpent</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/Whore\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Whore\">whore</a>\",<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos53.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> in reference to Prince Oberyn's nickname of \"the Red Viper\".\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Known_paramours\">Known paramours</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Paramour&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Known paramours\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Tyanna_of_the_Tower\" title=\"Tyanna of the Tower\">Tyanna of the Tower</a>, to King <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> <small>(eventually married)</small></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Alys_Harroway\" title=\"Alys Harroway\">Alys Harroway</a>, to King Maegor I Targaryen<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> <small>(already married)</small></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Tyanna_of_the_Tower\" title=\"Tyanna of the Tower\">Tyanna of the Tower</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Alys_Harroway\" title=\"Alys Harroway\">Alys Harroway</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> <small>(rumored)</small></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Mysaria\" title=\"Mysaria\">Mysaria</a>, to Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf45.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf45.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Harwin_Strong\" title=\"Harwin Strong\">Harwin Strong</a>, to Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf45.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf45.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup> <small>(rumored)</small></li>\n<li>Unnamed paramour, to King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon II Targaryen\">Aegon II Targaryen</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab13.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Unnamed <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">lowborn</a> paramour, to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Humfrey_Bracken\" title=\"Humfrey Bracken\">Humfrey Bracken</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Unnamed favorite mistress, to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Jason_Lannister\" title=\"Jason Lannister\">Jason Lannister</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Sylvenna_Sand\" title=\"Sylvenna Sand\">Sylvenna Sand</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Essie\" title=\"Essie\">Essie</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf795_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf795-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Samantha_Tarly\" title=\"Samantha Tarly\">Samantha Tarly</a>, to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Lyonel_Hightower\" title=\"Lyonel Hightower\">Lyonel Hightower</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup> <small>(eventually married)</small></li>\n<li>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Velaryon\" title=\"Alyn Velaryon\">Alyn Velaryon</a>, to Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Aliandra_Martell\" title=\"Aliandra Martell\">Aliandra Martell</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup> <small>(rumored)</small></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Rue\" title=\"Rue\">Rue</a>, to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Velaryon\" title=\"Alyn Velaryon\">Alyn Velaryon</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab22.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup> <small>(rumored)</small></li>\n<li>Unnamed mistress, to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Leowyn_Corbray\" title=\"Leowyn Corbray\">Leowyn Corbray</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab20.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>The nine mistresses of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_IV_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon IV Targaryen\">Aegon IV Targaryen</a>:<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf411.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf411.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<div style=\"columns:200px 2; width:50%\">\n<ol><li>Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Falena_Stokeworth\" title=\"Falena Stokeworth\">Falena Stokeworth</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Megette\" title=\"Megette\">Megette</a></li>\n<li>Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Cassella_Vaith\" title=\"Cassella Vaith\">Cassella Vaith</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Bellegere_Otherys\" title=\"Bellegere Otherys\">Bellegere Otherys</a></li>\n<li>Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Barba_Bracken\" title=\"Barba Bracken\">Barba Bracken</a></li>\n<li>Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Melissa_Blackwood\" title=\"Melissa Blackwood\">Melissa Blackwood</a></li>\n<li>Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Bethany_Bracken\" title=\"Bethany Bracken\">Bethany Bracken</a></li>\n<li>Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Jeyne_Lothston\" title=\"Jeyne Lothston\">Jeyne Lothston</a></li>\n<li>Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Serenei_of_Lys\" title=\"Serenei of Lys\">Serenei of Lys</a></li></ol></div>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Shiera_Seastar\" title=\"Shiera Seastar\">Shiera Seastar</a>, to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Brynden_Rivers\" title=\"Brynden Rivers\">Brynden Rivers</a><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtss.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiaf413.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiaf413.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.